This wouldn't play in any of my DVD players. All it did was show a green screen full of static. So I stuck it in my laptop to see if it would at least play in it. No luck. First thing it popped up a window that said it was coded for China. My program gave me the option of what region to set it for so I set it for the US. Got nothing, not even a title screen, just a plain black screen. So I reset to play it in region China. Then I did get the audio but instead of video it was like a slide show set at about a half second per photo.
I have 5 different DVD players including one Blu-Ray player and one combo VHS & DVD player. Tried it in every one of them and all could get was a green screen with a bunch of static on it. They looked kinda like the computer screens in The Matrix movies. So this one is going back. It's a real bummer too cuz I was really looking forward to watching this one.

This is a fun and funny movie.  While the characters are my much older than the purported high school age kids, most males can identify with the awkwardness and inability to fit in.

Barely Legal isn't a great movie by any means, but there's a few good laughs and you will root for the underdogs.
